{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9fb8847f-8361-4327-89b4-fe5b4c0a9ed1","content":"Here's the recommended setup for MSTest with parallel execution and sequential database tests.\n\n**1. Project file — `MyTests.csproj`**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package (v3+) includes the SDK, runner, and framework — no need for three separate package references.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution globally — add to any file (e.g. `Usings.cs`):**\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs test **classes** in parallel (each class still runs its methods sequentially). Use `ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` if you want methods parallelized too.\n\n**3. Mark database tests as sequential:**\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Test_InsertRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Test_ReadRecord() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n`[DoNotParallelize]` ensures that class runs alone — no other tests execute concurrently with it.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `ClassLevel` parallelism is the safer default (no shared state issues within a class)\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` applies to the entire class and also blocks other parallel classes while it runs\n- No `.runsettings` file needed — attributes are simpler and live with the code","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2d856ca6-f13a-4577-b96b-d19218d6d3ab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and there are no plugins. Let me just provide the user with the recommended MSTest setup based on my knowledge. This is a general .NET/MSTest question.\n\nHere's what I'll recommend:\n\n1. **Simplest `.csproj`** — use `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with MSTest (modern MSTest v3 uses `MSTest` meta-package).\n\n2. **Parallel by default** — MSTest supports parallelism via `[assembly: Parallelize]` attribute or via `.runsettings`.\n\n3. **Sequential database tests** — Use `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute on the test class.\n\n\nNow I'll create the example files to show them how this works in practice.","outputTokens":613,"requestId":"1BC8:17551C:23ABFBF:276EDB7:6A03DA2D"},"id":"2446bd29-74a0-41c0-aefa-b4fa48fd163f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:56:11.586Z","parentId":"54e47c71-6e75-444b-b9d7-03194635a5f5"}
